{"lemma":"أَنْبارٌ","slug":"أَنْبارٌ","root":"ن.ب.ر","root_slug":"ن-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39221","n39223"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise, to lift"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow, to flourish, to develop","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise one's voice","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shout at"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bite or sting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَبَرَ (nabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"accentuation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tick"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39221","headword_ar":"نَبَرَ","root":"nbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naborN","text_ar":"نَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything, T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing: (T, S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naborN","text_ar":"نَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies specially the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raising of the voice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, from the first part of the Keshsháf:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of the voice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so with the Arabs; and one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabara Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"نَبَرَ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naborapN","text_ar":"نَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the man spoke in a high tone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabara","text_ar":"نَبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naborapN","text_ar":"نَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered a sound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and [the inf. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naborapN","text_ar":"نَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crying out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shouting, from fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naborapu Almugan~iY","text_ar":"نَبْرَةُ المُغَنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the singer's raising his voice from a low to a high pitch."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabara AlHarofa","text_ar":"نَبَرَ الحَرْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naborN","text_ar":"نَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pronounced the letter with hemz"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hamoz","text_ar":"هَمْز"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (S, M, A, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurayo$N","text_ar":"قُرَيْشٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tanobiru","text_ar":"لَا تَنْبِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tribe of Kureysh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"do not pronounce with hemz."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) A man said to the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA nabiYo'a A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"يَا نَبِىْءَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O Prophet of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tanobiro yiA@somiY","text_ar":"لَا تَنْبِرْ يِا@سْمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pronounce not thou my name with hemz:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) for the tribe of Kureysh did not pronounce with hemz. (TA.) And when ElMahdee performed the pilgrimage, he preferred El-Kisáee to recite the prayers in El-Medeeneh, and the people of that city disapproved of his pronouncing with hemz, asking him wherefore he did so in reciting the Kur-án in the mosque of the Apostle of God. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","A","K","IAmb","M"]},{"entry_id":"n39223","headword_ar":"نِبْرٌ","root":"nbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anobaArN","text_ar":"اَنْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,) which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Heaps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akodaAsN","text_ar":"اَكْدَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, S,) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAm","text_ar":"طَعَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K, MS,) meaning of wheat, and of barley, [or other corn,] and of dates: (MS:) or [in the TA, and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"granaries"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahoraA='","text_ar":"اَهْرَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":") of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAm","text_ar":"طَعَام"},{"kind":"text","text":": (in the present day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a granary:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huroYN","text_ar":"هُرْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niborN","text_ar":"نِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TEAm","text_ar":"طعام"},{"kind":"text","text":", when poured in its place, rises: and the pl. pl. [i. e. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnbAr","text_ar":"انبار"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAbiyru","text_ar":"اَنَابِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anobaArN","text_ar":"اَنْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A merchant's magazine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which he puts together, in order,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piles up, his goods."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) [In the K, it is added, that the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niborN","text_ar":"نِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this addition seems to be misplaced: for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnbAr","text_ar":"انبار"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the last of the senses here explained, as well as when applied to a granary. and to a collection of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TEAm","text_ar":"طعام"},{"kind":"text","text":", appears to be a pl. without a sing.]"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","K","MS"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}